---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Accessibility Statement" description="MERIDIAN's commitment to digital accessibility and how to report barriers on this site.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-[720px] px-6 pb-32 pt-40 md:px-10 md:pb-40 md:pt-52" data-reveal-group>
    <p data-reveal class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brass">Legal</p>
    <h1 data-reveal class="mt-4 font-display text-[clamp(2rem,4.5vw,3.25rem)] leading-[1.05] text-ink">
      Accessibility Statement
    </h1>
    <p data-reveal class="mt-4 text-sm uppercase tracking-wide text-stone">
      Last updated: July 13, 2026
    </p>

    <!-- PLACEHOLDER: illustrative accessibility statement -- have qualified legal/accessibility counsel review before publishing live -->
    <p data-reveal class="mt-8 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone">
      MERIDIAN is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people
      of all abilities. We are continually improving the user experience
      of meridian-example.com (the "Site") for everyone, and we apply
      relevant accessibility standards as part of that effort.
    </p>

    <h2 data-reveal class="mt-12 font-display text-2xl text-ink">Conformance Status</h2>
    <p data-reveal class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone">
      The Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) define
      requirements for designers and developers to improve accessibility
      for people with disabilities. Our target conformance level is
      WCAG 2.1, Level AA. This Site is intended to be largely conformant
      with this standard, meaning the content meets the standard in most
      respects, with a small number of known exceptions noted below.
    </p>

    <h2 data-reveal class="mt-12 font-display text-2xl text-ink">Measures We Take to Support Accessibility</h2>
    <ul data-reveal class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone">
      <li>Semantic HTML structure, with a logical heading hierarchy on every page;</li>
      <li>Descriptive alternative text on meaningful images, and decorative images marked as such for assistive technology;</li>
      <li>Full keyboard operability for navigation, menus, dropdowns, forms, and the image gallery, including visible focus states;</li>
      <li>A focus trap and Escape-to-close behavior on the mobile navigation menu and other overlay dialogs;</li>
      <li>Color combinations checked against WCAG contrast requirements for text and interactive elements;</li>
      <li>Motion and animation that respect the "prefers-reduced-motion" setting in your browser or operating system, with a static fallback for every animated component;</li>
      <li>Labeled form fields and clear error and confirmation states on our forms.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 data-reveal class="mt-12 font-display text-2xl text-ink">Known Limitations</h2>
    <p data-reveal class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone">
      Despite our best efforts, some content on this Site may not yet be
      fully accessible. Known limitations include:
    </p>
    <ul data-reveal class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone">
      <li>Embedded third-party content, such as the Google Maps embed on the Neighborhood page, is governed by that provider's own accessibility practices, which are outside our direct control;</li>
      <li>Placeholder imagery used during development is labeled descriptively but will be replaced with final photography and refreshed alt text prior to full launch;</li>
      <li>Some older browsers may not fully support the motion and layout techniques used on this Site.</li>
    </ul>
    <p data-reveal class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone">
      We are actively working to address these limitations as the Site
      continues to develop.
    </p>

    <h2 data-reveal class="mt-12 font-display text-2xl text-ink">Compatibility</h2>
    <p data-reveal class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone">
      This Site is designed to be compatible with recent versions of
      major browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge) and with
      commonly used assistive technologies, including screen readers
      such as VoiceOver, NVDA, and JAWS.
    </p>

    <h2 data-reveal class="mt-12 font-display text-2xl text-ink">Feedback</h2>
    <p data-reveal class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone">
      We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of this Site. If you
      encounter an accessibility barrier, please let us know:
    </p>
    <!-- TODO: real contact info -->
    <address class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone not-italic">
      MERIDIAN<br />
      2 South Bayshore Drive, Suite 200<br />
      Coconut Grove, Miami, FL 33133<br />
      <a href="mailto:hello@meridian-example.com" class="transition-colors duration-300 hover:text-brass">hello@meridian-example.com</a><br />
      <a href="tel:+13055550100" class="transition-colors duration-300 hover:text-brass">+1 (305) 555-0100</a>
    </address>
    <p data-reveal class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone">
      We try to respond to accessibility feedback within a few business
      days and will do our best to identify a solution consistent with
      applicable law.
    </p>

    <p data-reveal class="mt-12 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone/80">
      This statement is illustrative placeholder content prepared for
      site development purposes and has not been reviewed by legal or
      accessibility counsel. It should be reviewed and finalized,
      ideally alongside an independent accessibility audit, before this
      page is published live.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
